In evaluating the expected and actual loss ratios, the Commissioner shall consider:
the statistical credibility of incurred claims experience and earned premiums;
the period for which rates are computed to provide coverage;
experienced and projected trends;
the concentration of experience within early policy duration;
expected claim fluctuation;
experienced refunds, adjustments, or dividends;
renewability features;
all appropriate expense factors;
interest;
the experimental nature of the coverage;
policy reserves;
the mix of business by risk classification; and
product features, including long elimination periods, high deductibles, and high maximum limits.
